- What can I do for you?
- I'm reporting for duty.

729
01:02:22,772 --> 01:02:26,481
- You're a few days early, captain.
- Any duty, sir.

730
01:02:26,676 --> 01:02:30,249
Sorry. Not much left to do but wait.

731
01:02:30,413 --> 01:02:32,893
But you're welcome to wait here.

732
01:02:33,783 --> 01:02:36,127
I've read your record, Yindel.

733
01:02:36,285 --> 01:02:38,959
- You're a good cop.
- Thank you, sir.

734
01:02:39,122 --> 01:02:42,069
Truth is, you've been a hero of mine
since I was a kid.

735
01:02:42,225 --> 01:02:45,570
The only thing I don't understand
is haw far apart we are on Batman.

736
01:02:46,129 --> 01:02:48,735
Then let's not talk about Batman.

737
01:02:49,398 --> 01:02:54,074
- Of course we heard about the pipe.
- Of course you did. Whatever.

738
01:02:56,639 --> 01:03:01,281
I don't understand haw you can support
a vigilante. Our job is to uphold the law.

739
01:03:01,444 --> 01:03:02,445
No thanks.

740
01:03:03,446 --> 01:03:06,290
Wife made me quit the cigars.

741
01:03:08,284 --> 01:03:13,597
I'm sure you've hears old fossils like me
talk about Pearl Harbor? Mostly, we all lie.

742
01:03:13,756 --> 01:03:15,702
Make it sound like we leapt to our feet...

743
01:03:15,858 --> 01:03:18,168
...and went after the Axis
the second it happened.

744
01:03:18,327 --> 01:03:20,466
Truth is, we were scared stiff.

745
01:03:20,630 --> 01:03:23,110
Rumors were flying, we barely had an army.

746
01:03:23,266 --> 01:03:27,612
Hell, we were hiding in our beds
with our heads under the sheets.

747
01:03:28,371 --> 01:03:31,978
And then we heard President Roosevelt
on the radio.

748
01:03:32,141 --> 01:03:35,122
That voice, strong and sure...

749
01:03:35,278 --> 01:03:39,454
...taking our fear
and turning it into a fighting spirit.

750
01:03:39,982 --> 01:03:42,622
He's why we wan that war.

751
01:03:47,824 --> 01:03:51,397
MUTANT 1: You ain't heard about the pipe?
Leader says everyone.

752
01:03:51,561 --> 01:03:54,371
MUTANT 2:
We heard, we heard. We're on our way.

753
01:03:56,265 --> 01:03:57,903
Years later, this report came out...

754
01:03:58,067 --> 01:04:00,911
...that Roosevelt might have known
Pearl Harbor was coming...

755
01:04:01,070 --> 01:04:04,916
...and let it happen.
That rattled around in my head for days.

756
01:04:05,074 --> 01:04:08,146
How horrible it would be if it were true.

757
01:04:08,311 --> 01:04:11,724
Then again, it's what get us into the war.

758
01:04:11,881 --> 01:04:13,918
A lot of men died.

759
01:04:14,083 --> 01:04:17,189
But in the end it saved millions.

760
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:20,196
I bounced back and forth like that...

761
01:04:20,356 --> 01:04:22,165
...until I realized...

762
01:04:22,325 --> 01:04:24,931
...it was too big for me to judge.

763
01:04:25,094 --> 01:04:27,040
He was too big.

764
01:04:27,196 --> 01:04:30,700
I still don't see
what that has to do with Batman.

765
01:04:30,867 --> 01:04:32,107
Maybe one day, you will.

766
01:04:32,301 --> 01:04:33,439
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

767
01:04:33,936 --> 01:04:36,348
Commissioner, you better see this.

768
01:04:37,907 --> 01:04:40,444
- Where to?
- Take the cycle back to the cave.

769
01:04:40,610 --> 01:04:44,752
- You're done for tonight.
- How do you know it worked?

770
01:04:54,223 --> 01:04:58,399
GORDON: There must be thousands of them.
Why? Why there?

771
01:04:58,561 --> 01:05:02,099
- Because I want them there.
- It'll take an army to surround them.

772
01:05:02,265 --> 01:05:03,938
I could call in the National Guard.

773
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:06,979
No. You can't arrest and hold them all.

774
01:05:07,136 --> 01:05:10,743
The only way to finish this is to defeat them.
Humiliate them.

775
01:05:11,274 --> 01:05:15,347
I'm counting on you, Jim. One last time.

776
01:05:18,080 --> 01:05:22,620
You get kids, Officer Thompson, badge 5861?

777
01:05:23,386 --> 01:05:26,458
- Shut up.
- Just asking.

778
01:05:26,622 --> 01:05:29,102
I love kids. How about a wife?

779
01:05:29,258 --> 01:05:33,968
You get a sweet little wife
all alone at home, 5861?

780
01:05:34,130 --> 01:05:37,805
- I said shut up.
- Thompson. Go get some air.

781
01:05:38,367 --> 01:05:40,438
With pleasure.

782
01:05:42,805 --> 01:05:49,586
- Came down to say hello, old man?
- No. I came to say goodbye.

783
01:06:14,670 --> 01:06:15,705
[LEADER GRUNTS]

784
01:06:37,660 --> 01:06:38,695
[MUTANTS MURMURING]

785
01:06:46,135 --> 01:06:48,137
[MURMURING CONTINUES]

786
01:06:55,711 --> 01:06:57,315
[LEADER GRUNTS]

787
01:07:03,452 --> 01:07:04,954
[YELLS]

788
01:07:12,094 --> 01:07:14,836
Batman. Show yourself.

789
01:07:14,997 --> 01:07:17,773
Face me, fool, and I will kill you.

790
01:07:17,967 --> 01:07:21,346
I will show you who rules Gotham City.

791
01:07:21,504 --> 01:07:24,508
Okay, son. Show me.

792
01:07:27,710 --> 01:07:29,712
[GRUNTING]

793
01:07:38,421 --> 01:07:41,425
You're weak, old man. You're slow.

794
01:07:41,590 --> 01:07:46,061
True, but we're all slow
when we're thigh high deep in mud.

795
01:07:51,801 --> 01:07:54,372
And you're not too bright.

796
01:08:18,594 --> 01:08:19,664
What was that?

797
01:08:19,829 --> 01:08:21,968
Just the right kind of cut
above the eyes.

798
01:08:22,898 --> 01:08:25,401
The kind that bleeds.

799
01:08:30,406 --> 01:08:33,148
Ah. You see, Dan? Batman nasty.

800
01:08:33,309 --> 01:08:34,617
MUTANT 1:
Shh.

801
01:08:34,777 --> 01:08:37,587
- Leader's bagging.
- Leader billy berserk, Rob.

802
01:08:37,746 --> 01:08:40,818
- He peg Batman, you see.
MUTANT 1: Shh.

803
01:08:41,050 --> 01:08:43,052
[PANTING]

804
01:09:07,143 --> 01:09:08,588
[SCREAMS]

805
01:09:27,029 --> 01:09:28,064
That a tickle?

806
01:09:28,230 --> 01:09:30,335
That was a nerve bundle in your deltoid.

807
01:09:30,499 --> 01:09:33,412
Might not hurt, but you won't
be moving that arm for a while.

808
01:09:36,038 --> 01:09:37,642
[YELLS]

809
01:09:46,115 --> 01:09:48,652
He dusted. Batman dusted.

810
01:09:48,817 --> 01:09:50,854
Batman don't shiv. You see.

811
01:09:53,856 --> 01:09:57,065
You finished, old man.

812
01:09:57,927 --> 01:09:59,270
You don't get it, son.

813
01:09:59,428 --> 01:10:02,170
This isn't a mud hole.

814
01:10:07,570 --> 01:10:10,414
It's an operating table.

815
01:10:12,174 --> 01:10:13,448
And I'm the surgeon.

816
01:10:13,642 --> 01:10:14,950
[SCREAMS]

817
01:10:22,384 --> 01:10:23,761
[BONES CRUNCH]

818
01:10:27,723 --> 01:10:29,725
[BLOWS LANDING]

819
01:10:52,314 --> 01:10:55,921
The Mutants are dead.
This is the new face of the law.

820
01:10:56,085 --> 01:10:57,894
We are the Sans of Batman.

821
01:10:58,053 --> 01:11:00,624
And Gotham's criminals
are about to enter hell.

822
01:11:00,789 --> 01:11:02,097
It worked.

823
01:11:04,059 --> 01:11:07,802
We rounded up about half of them,
no fight left in them at all.

824
01:11:07,963 --> 01:11:10,466
Those that get away have broken off
into smaller gangs.

825
01:11:10,633 --> 01:11:13,580
I'll deal with the rest of them in time.

826
01:11:13,736 --> 01:11:16,649
You'll be doing that on your own.
Good luck, Bruce.

827
01:11:16,805 --> 01:11:18,910
You're gonna need it.

828
01:11:33,088 --> 01:11:35,295
I'm telling you, I didn't do nothing.

829
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:56,055
Instances of Batman-inspired vigilantism
are on the rise.

830
01:11:56,245 --> 01:11:59,818
Regular people lighting to take back
their neighborhoods.

831
01:12:00,349 --> 01:12:02,386
How are you feeling, sir?

832
01:12:02,551 --> 01:12:05,464
I know I should have been afraid.
But this is my black.

833
01:12:05,621 --> 01:12:08,295
The guy was mugging a lady
in front of my shop.

834
01:12:09,558 --> 01:12:11,765
Like it was yesterday.

835
01:12:12,027 --> 01:12:16,567
Exactly as I warned, the Batman has infected
the minds of Gotham's youth.

836
01:12:16,765 --> 01:12:19,371
Poisoned these so-called
"Sons of Batman

837
01:12:19,535 --> 01:12:23,677
...with an insidious excuse
for the most violently anti-social behavior.

838
01:12:24,206 --> 01:12:26,914
Batman? I'm tired of hearing about him.

839
01:12:27,076 --> 01:12:30,649
Why can't he just let things go,
the way the rest of us do?

840
01:12:30,813 --> 01:12:32,053
We count too.

841
01:12:32,214 --> 01:12:34,251
A bunch of psychopaths
turn on criminals...

842
01:12:34,416 --> 01:12:37,056
...instead of the rest of us,
and you wanna blame Batman?

843
01:12:37,219 --> 01:12:39,426
I say more power to them.

844
01:12:39,855 --> 01:12:45,100
Do not expect any further statements.
The Sons of Batman do not make speeches.

845
01:12:45,294 --> 01:12:47,103
- We act.
- Batman...?

846
01:12:47,296 --> 01:12:50,869
- Gotham City belongs to the Batman.
- Batman.

847
01:12:51,033 --> 01:12:52,740
Batman.

848
01:12:53,402 --> 01:12:56,383
Darling.

